    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese painting technique, popular in the Heian (794-1185) and Kamakura (1185-1333) periods, where layers of opaque color are applied over an underdrawing. Ink lines are then carefully redrawn and facial features are added. This technique is associated with "yamato-e" and was the technique used in the creation of The Tale of Genji handscroll.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
